# Build context lives at the atlantis/ root. Everything not needed
# inside the Docker build context is excluded here — the alternative
# (transferring it and then ignoring it inside Dockerfile COPY) costs
# every build the transfer time. The previous unfiltered context was
# ~87 MB dominated by `bin/` (47 MB of host-arch dev binaries the
# Dockerfile never references).

# Git metadata — never needed for the build, large.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Host-arch build outputs — the Dockerfile compiles fresh in-container.
bin/

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode
*.swp

# Local env files — `.env` is for `make dev` (host-side), the container
# reads env from docker-compose.yml. Never bake secrets into images.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs + caches
*.log
.cache
node_modules

# Docs that don't change the build
*.md
docs/

# Tests' large fixtures don't ship in the runtime binary either; the
# `go build ./cmd/server` only needs the import graph. Test files
# themselves are skipped by `go build` so we keep _test.go files in
# context (they're tiny and excluding them via dockerignore breaks
# `go test` inside the container if anyone runs it).
tests/integration/testdata/large
